  "text": "In case of an inferior dislocation, the dislocation is first converted to a subcoracoid type by flexing the affected arm 15e20 and lowering the affected shoulder in the coronal plane by 15e20 by tilting the table or placing a sandbag under the unaffected shoulder. Then, the dislocation can be reduced in the same manner as an anterior dislocation. [CITATION_1] ",
